% X-LABEL(1) 0.0
% Sebastian Schwarz <seschwar@googlemail.com>
% 2010-06-10

# NAME

x-label -- edit email keywords/labels/tags stored in a message header field

# SYNOPSIS

`x-label` [*options*] [\--] [*command* [*label*]...]

# DESCRIPTION

`x-label` reads a single email message from standard input, searches for a X-Label or other specified header fields, modifies them according to the given command and outputs the modified message with the new header fields at the bottom of the email header section to the standard output.

`x-label` automatically removes any duplicate labels and combines multiple read header fields.

# OPTIONS

-c, \--catenate
:   Catenate the mail headers instead of refolding them to fit the 78 characters per line limit.

-h, \--help
:   Print usage information.

-f *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*, \--from *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*, -i *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*, \--input *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*
:   Read and parse the *HEADER* by splitting it on *SEPARATOR*.
    If given multiple times the parsed labels from all *HEADER*s will be joined before being processed.
    If this option is not specified `x-label` defaults to `--input X-Label ','`.

-o *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*, \--output *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*, -t *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*, \--to *HEADER* *SEPARATOR*
:   Print the processed labels in the field body of *HEADER* as a list separated by *SEPARATOR*.
    If specified multiple times all *HEADER*s will be printed with the complete set of labels.
    If this option is not specified `x-label` defaults to `--output X-Label ', '`.

-v, \--version
:   Print version information.

# COMMANDS

add
:   Adds the given labels to the header field body.

clear
:   Deletes all specified header fields.

set
:   Overwrites the header field body with the given labels.

remove
:   Removes the specified labels from the header field body.

tidy
:   Tidies the specified header field(s) removing duplicates and odd formatting.

# BUGS

`x-label` strips trailing whitespace characters from the header fields.
It also does not use MIME de- and encoding on the label header fields.

If you find more bugs, please report them at <http://bitbucket.org/seschwar/x-label/issues>.

# EXAMPLES

Combine Mutt's X-Label and Thunderbird's X-Mozilla-Keys header fields into the standardized Keywords header field:

    x-label --from X-Label , --from X-Mozilla-Keys ' ' tidy

Synchronize Dovecot's X-Keywords, Mutt's X-Label and Thunderbird's X-Mozilla-Keys header fields:

    x-label -i X-Keywords ' ' -i X-Label , -i X-Mozilla-Keys ' ' -o X-Keywords ' ' -o X-Label ', ' -o X-Mozilla-Keys ' ' tidy

# SEE ALSO

`formail`(1), `maildirkw`(1), `reformail`(1), RFC 822, RFC 2822

Homepage: <http://bitbucket.org/seschwar/x-label>

